# MR Execution Result Report Rule

This rule defines that **under any circumstances**, when AI (Cursor) creates or submits an MR, it must provide an execution result report in the chat in the user's preferred language.

## Applicable Scenarios

This rule applies to **any circumstance** where AI creates or submits an MR, including but not limited to:
- `cr` command
- `cr-single-ticket` command
- Any situation where an MR is created via the `auto-commit-and-mr.md` flow
- Situations where an MR is created by manually running the `create-mr` script
- Any other method or command used by AI to create or submit an MR
- **Regardless of what method or tool is used, this rule must be followed whenever AI creates or submits an MR**

## Core Principle

**CRITICAL**: **Under any circumstances**, after AI (Cursor) successfully creates or submits an MR, it **MUST** provide a formatted execution result report in chat in the user's preferred language (Chinese or English). This rule has no exceptions and applies to all scenarios where AI creates or submits an MR.

## Execution Result Format

The execution result must include the following three main sections:

### 1. Commit Information

Display detailed commit info:
- **Type**: commit type (e.g., `feat`, `fix`, `chore`, etc.)
- **Ticket**: Jira ticket number, **must use hyperlink format** (e.g., `[FE-7846](https://innotech.atlassian.net/browse/FE-7846)`)
- **Message**: commit message
- **Commit Hash**: full hash of the commit (e.g., `80a9ac740a`)

**Note**: If the commit message contains multiple tickets, all tickets must be displayed in hyperlink format.

### 2. Merge Request Information

Display detailed MR info:
- **MR Link**: full URL of the GitLab MR, **must use hyperlink format** (e.g., `[MR !3177](https://gitlab.service-hub.tech/frontend/fluid-two/-/merge_requests/3177)`)
- **MR ID**: ID of the MR (e.g., `!3177`)
- **Title**: title of the MR (including Draft prefix if applicable)
- **Status**: status of the MR (e.g., `Draft`)
- **Reviewer**: reviewer of the MR (e.g., `@royng`)
- **Labels**: labels of the MR (e.g., `FE Board`, `AI`, etc.)
- **Associated Jira**: associated Jira ticket, **must use hyperlink format** (e.g., `[FE-7846](https://innotech.atlassian.net/browse/FE-7846)`). If there are multiple tickets, each must be shown in hyperlink format, separated by commas (e.g., `[FE-7846](https://innotech.atlassian.net/browse/FE-7846), [IN-1234](https://innotech.atlassian.net/browse/IN-1234)`)
- **AI Review**: submission status of the AI review (e.g., `Automatically submitted` or `Not submitted`)

**CRITICAL**: All Jira tickets and MR links must use Markdown hyperlink format `[display text](URL)`, ensuring users can click directly to navigate.

### 3. Changed Content

List files changed in this update with descriptions:
- **New**: list of added files, each with a brief description
- **Updated**: list of updated files, each with a brief description
- **Reverted**: list of reverted files (if any), each with a brief description

